related_questions.question: When should I evolve Pansear?
related_questions.title: AI Overview
list: Consider your desired moveset: Look at the moves Pansear learns naturally and compare it to what Simisear can learn. If there are moves Pansear learns that you want, wait until it learns those moves before evolving.

Fire Stone evolutions: In most Pokemon games, Pokemon evolved by stones (like Simisear from Pansear) do not learn many new moves after evolving. This is why it's crucial to evolve it at the right time.
TMs and HMs: Remember that you can still teach your evolved Pokemon moves using Technical Machines (TMs) and Hidden Machines (HMs), even if they don't learn them by level-up.
Move Relearner: Some games have a move relearner NPC that can teach your Pokemon moves it has previously learned, but this usually doesn't work for moves it wouldn't naturally learn.

Game-specific considerations: Some Pokemon games have specific levels where certain moves are learned. For example, in Pokemon Black and White, Pansear learns Fire Blast at level 34 and Crunch at level 43.
